<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0047 </DOCNO><TEXT>A heterojunction p-i-n photovoltaic cell having at least three layersof different semiconductor materials is described composed together ofat least four different elements, comprising: a p-type, relatively wideband gap semiconductor layer; a high resistivity intrinsic semiconductorlayer, used as an absorber of light radiation; an n-type, relativelywide band gap semiconductor layer; the intrinsic layer being in electricallyconductive contact on one side with the p-type layer and on an oppositeside with the n-type layer; and first and second ohmic contacts in electricallyconductive contact with the p-type layer and the n-type layer, respectively.</TEXT></DOC>